{
  "text": "Patients in the INFORMS trial exhibited very low levels of inflammatory activity at baseline and throughout the trial. Low inflammatory MRI activity together with the observed low relapse rate is consistent with the currently accepted definition of PPMS. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Despite the low level of inflammatory activity at the time of inclusion and thereafter, patients had a substantial T2 lesion volume at baseline, indicating previous inflammatory activity, and a high progression rate on-study, with accelerated brain volume loss. The clinical disease course was well reflected in the rate of brain volume loss, which was most rapid in the severe subgroup who experienced ≥2 confirmed progressions and least rapid in the stable subgroup who experienced no confirmed progressions. These results confirm a relationship between brain volume loss and disability ",
